# Day 12 – HTTP in Detail

## Room
HTTP in Detail

## Platform
TryHackMe

## Objective
Learn how the Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) works, how web browsers communicate with web servers, and understand the structure of HTTP requests and responses.

## What I Learned
- What HTTP is and how it powers web communication
- The difference between HTTP and HTTPS
- Structure of HTTP requests and responses
- Common HTTP methods:
  - GET
  - POST
  - PUT
  - DELETE
- HTTP status codes (200, 301, 404, 500, etc.)
- HTTP headers and their purpose
- Cookies and session management
- Basic client-server communication

## Key Takeaways
- HTTP is a stateless application-layer protocol.
- HTTPS encrypts communication using TLS/SSL, making web browsing secure.
- Status codes help identify whether a request was successful or if an error occurred.
- Understanding HTTP is essential for web application security and penetration testing.

## Reflection
This room helped me understand how browsers and web servers communicate. Learning HTTP fundamentals is an important step toward understanding web application security and becoming a SOC Analyst.

